    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="832"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d832">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">390.1115/6284: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-12">March 12,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>599. American interests—China. Department’s 107, January 14. Request Swiss
                    Government to continue to press Japanese Government to restore military rank to
                    Cunningham and Smith in compliance with Article 49 of Geneva Prisoners of War
                    Convention and to accord to these men the treatment provided for officer
                    prisoners of war by this Convention.</p>
                <p>Ask Swiss to take the necessary steps to see that these men receive such
                    financial assistance as may be necessary in the circumstances.<note n="24"
                        xml:id="d832fn24">In telegram No. 2997, May 15, the Minister in Switzerland
                        stated that Cunningham and Smith retained their rank and that the
                        regulations of the prison where they were detained determined whether they
                        were permitted to receive money or supplies (390.1115/7409).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
